author: VR Gorilla - Virtual Reality & 360 Videos
description:
Welcome to Sequoia National Park — a place of mammoth trees, ancient history, and natural beauty. Obviously, the park is mainly known for its towering giants, and one specimen in particular, which is the largest tree on Earth. During this tour, we’ll travel from the foothill town of Three Rivers up into the mountains, exploring this unique ecosystem.

Click the *Join* button now to become a VR Gorilla YouTube member, unlocking access to the full video and our complete collection of full-length videos. https://www.youtube.com/channel/UC6AXBF-78lNa3_TjAIWZWmQ/join
